  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero-bg pt-32 pb-20 px-6 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-sm font-medium tracking-widest uppercase mb-4" style="color:#D6CE93">For Restaurants &amp; Eateries</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold leading-tight mb-6 text-white">
        Your food.<br/>Our baskets.<br/>Forest Park.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl mb-10 leading-relaxed" style="color:#EFEBCE">
        The magicians behind the food in every ForestParkPicnics.com basket are the amazing chefs and eateries we find right here in the CWE and The Grove. Is this you?
      </p>
      <a href="#steps"
         class="inline-block px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-charcoal font-bold text-base hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity"
         style="background-color:#D6CE93">
        See How It Works
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE PITCH -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6" style="background:#EFEBCE">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed" style="color:#1C1C1C">
        We set out to support our local restaurant community — not just by buying their food for our guests during <strong>off-peak hours</strong>, but by putting that food in front of people who wouldn't have tried it otherwise and helping them earn new fans right here in St. Louis.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base" style="color:#607466">
        $5 from every booking goes to <strong>Forest Park Forever</strong>. Your food helps keep the park thriving.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 3 STEPS -->
  <section id="steps" class="py-20 px-6 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-14" style="color:#1C1C1C">
        3 Steps to Becoming an Entrée Partner
      </h2>

      <!-- Step 1 -->
      <div class="flex gap-6 mb-12">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg text-white" style="background:#628395">1</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2" style="color:#1C1C1C">Reserve your month.</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600 mb-3">
            Tell us you're interested and which month(s) work for your kitchen. You don't need to know what you'll put in our&nbsp;5×7.5" box just yet.
          </p>
          <a href="/partners/apply"
             class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 font-semibold text-sm hover:opacity-75 transition-opacity"
             style="color:#628395">
            Reserve your month
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M14 5l7 7m0 0l-7 7m7-7H3"/></svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 2 -->
      <div class="flex gap-6 mb-12">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg text-white" style="background:#628395">2</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2" style="color:#1C1C1C">We'll drop off an empty box for you to test with.</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600 mb-3">
            When you're ready, let us know when to come pick it up and sample the contents. We test every entrée after one hour in the box before we commit.
          </p>
          <a href="/partners/design-guide"
             
             class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 font-semibold text-sm hover:opacity-75 transition-opacity"
             style="color:#628395">
            Read the Entrée Box Design Guide
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M14 5l7 7m0 0l-7 7m7-7H3"/></svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 3 -->
      <div class="flex gap-6">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-12 h-12 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-lg text-white" style="background:#628395">3</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2" style="color:#1C1C1C">We become your best customer for a month.</h3>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600 mb-3">
            Four days a week, all month long, your dish is the star of the show — in front of couples who've never been to your place and are about to want to.
          </p>
          <a href="/partners/operating-guide"
             
             class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 font-semibold text-sm hover:opacity-75 transition-opacity"
             style="color:#628395">
            Read the Partner Operating Guide
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M14 5l7 7m0 0l-7 7m7-7H3"/></svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6" style="background:#EFEBCE">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-12" style="color:#1C1C1C">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">

        <!-- Q1 -->
        <details class="bg-white rounded-xl px-6 py-5 shadow-sm">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-semibold text-base" style="color:#1C1C1C">
            Do I need to know what dish I'll make before signing up?
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="chevron w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0 ml-4" style="color:#628395" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
            Nope. Reserve your month first. We'll drop off an empty 5×7.5" stainless steel bento box so you can test with your kitchen before we finalize anything.
          </p>
        </details>

        <!-- Q2 -->
        <details class="bg-white rounded-xl px-6 py-5 shadow-sm">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-semibold text-base" style="color:#1C1C1C">
            How much food actually goes in the box?
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="chevron w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0 ml-4" style="color:#628395" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
            Less than you'd think — in the best way. Your box is the entrée course in a 3-course meal for two. There's already an appetizer and a pint of ice cream in the basket. Think 3–4 bites per person. Quality over quantity — you're not filling anyone up, you're wowing them.
          </p>
        </details>

        <!-- Q3 -->
        <details class="bg-white rounded-xl px-6 py-5 shadow-sm">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-semibold text-base" style="color:#1C1C1C">
            What does the day-to-day actually look like?
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="chevron w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0 ml-4" style="color:#628395" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
            We give you 3 hours advance notice of exact order quantity (8am for 11am pickups, 2pm for 5pm pickups). We come to your service entrance, drop off a red thermal bag with sanitized boxes and a check attached. You pack. We pick up promptly at 11am or 5pm. That's it — Wed through Sat.
          </p>
        </details>

        <!-- Q4 -->
        <details class="bg-white rounded-xl px-6 py-5 shadow-sm">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-semibold text-base" style="color:#1C1C1C">
            When and how do you pay?
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="chevron w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0 ml-4" style="color:#628395" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
            By check, upon pickup. The check for the day's order is attached to the front window of the thermal bag when we drop it off — you don't have to chase us for it.
          </p>
        </details>

        <!-- Q5 -->
        <details class="bg-white rounded-xl px-6 py-5 shadow-sm">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-semibold text-base" style="color:#1C1C1C">
            What if we need to change the dish mid-month?
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="chevron w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0 ml-4" style="color:#628395" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
            We ask for 7 days notice for any changes to the dish, pricing, or availability. Agreed dishes stay on for the full calendar month — consistency is important for guest expectations.
          </p>
        </details>

        <!-- Q6 -->
        <details class="bg-white rounded-xl px-6 py-5 shadow-sm">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-semibold text-base" style="color:#1C1C1C">
            How do picnickers find out about us?
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="chevron w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0 ml-4" style="color:#628395" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
            Every guest scans a QR code for their digital menu — featuring your dish, your story, and links to your website and Google reviews. We also write a feature post about your place on tourcwe.com. Not just new orders. New fans.
          </p>
        </details>

        <!-- Q7 -->
        <details class="bg-white rounded-xl px-6 py-5 shadow-sm">
          <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-semibold text-base" style="color:#1C1C1C">
            Do we need to provide napkins, cutlery, or condiments?
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="chevron w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0 ml-4" style="color:#628395" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
            No bags, napkins, cutlery, or condiments are included — unless the condiment was made in-house specifically for the dish. We handle everything else in the basket.
          </p>
        </details>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

